        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:28PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with frequent
lightning along a line extending from 11 miles south of Easley to 8
miles southwest of Anderson, and moving east at 25 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Anderson, Homeland Park, Belton, Honea Path, Iva, Starr, Anderson
Airport, Williamston, Northlake, and Broadway Lake.

In addition to intense lightning, very heavy rainfall rates up to 2
inches per hour and wind gusts to 40 mph will be possible in these
areas.
</description>
